The paper discusses optimization algorithms and their application in machine learning, specifically in approximating integrals in a reproducing kernel Hilbert space. This topic falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and optimization (cs.NA). The paper also discusses information theory (cs.IT) and control systems (cs.SY) in relation to the algorithms. Additionally, the paper explores the learning bias behind herding, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
